Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.83,0:01:05.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,大家好\N{\fs90}Hello, everybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.86,0:01:07.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,你好吗\N{\fs90}How are you? How are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.90,0:01:10.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,谢谢 很高兴见到你们 谢谢你们的到来\N{\fs90}Thank you. Good to see you. Thank you for coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.64,0:01:18.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,外面真冷\N{\fs90}Cold out there!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.84,0:01:20.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,太冷了\N{\fs90}That is cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.21,0:01:23.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,各位好\N{\fs90}Hello, everybody!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.78,0:01:26.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,你们好\N{\fs90}Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.96,0:01:29.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,欢迎来到 The Grand Tour \N{\fs90}Hello. Welcome to The GrandTour.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.01,0:01:31.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,圣诞快乐\N{\fs90}Happy Christmas.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.35,0:01:32.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,这周 我们来到了\N{\fs90}This week, we are coming -
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.75,0:01:36.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果你能看到窗外正下着淅淅沥沥的小雨\N{\fs90}if you can see through the drizzle dribbling down the windows -
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.29,0:01:37.66,字幕,,0,0,0,,这里是斯堪的纳维亚\N{\fs90}from Scandinavia.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.53,0:01:41.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦耶\N{\fs90}Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.07,0:01:43.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,当然 这里\N{\fs90}This, of course...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.53,0:01:46.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,这里是那些阴郁戏剧的故乡\N{\fs90}This, of course, is the home of those gloomy dramas
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.01,0:01:48.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,在这里一个穿着套头毛衣的怪女人\N{\fs90}where a weird woman in a jumper
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.77,0:01:50.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,盯着湖面看了六小时\N{\fs90} solves a murder
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.09,0:01:53.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后破了一起谋杀案\N{\fs90}by staring at a lake for six hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.17,0:01:56.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,这很有可能变成\N{\fs90}This will probably be the jolliest programme
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.49,0:01:58.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,自从四个葬礼和一个葬礼以后\N{\fs90}to come out of this neck of the woods since...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.63,0:01:59.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,这个地方最欢脱的节目\N{\fs90}Four Funerals And A Funeral .
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.89,0:02:01.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\fs90}- Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.18,0:02:03.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,那是瑞典的爱情喜剧\N{\fs90}Swedish rom-com that was. Erm...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.49,0:02:05.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,当哈利射了莎莉\N{\fs90}When Harry Shot Sally .
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.39,0:02:06.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,非常滑稽\N{\fs90}Oh, a laugh a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.04,0:02:09.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,戴珍珠项链的少女 不对\N{\fs90}The Girl With The Pearl Necklace. No.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.92,0:02:13.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,-那是另外一种斯堪的纳维亚电影  -真的假的\N{\fs90}-That's another sort of Scandinavian film. -Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.86,0:02:15.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\fs90}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.03,0:02:19.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,特别要强调的是\N{\fs90}Anyway, specifically,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.72,0:02:23.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们深入芬兰 这里在北极圈内\N{\fs90}we are deep inside the Arctic Circle in Finland.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.31,0:02:29.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,这就对了 而芬兰\N{\fs90}There you go. And Finland, of course...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.13,0:02:34.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,芬兰无疑是所有现任赛车手的故乡\N{\fs90}Finland, of course, is home to every single racing driver currently...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.42,0:02:36.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,-怎么了 -什么 所有人吗\N{\fs90}-What? -What, all of them?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.84,0:02:40.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,好吧 除了尼科 罗斯伯格 他是芬兰人\N{\fs90}Well, apart from Nico Rosberg, who is Finnish,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.41,0:02:42.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是不知道出于什么原因 宣称他是德国人\N{\fs90}but, for some reason, claims he's German.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.66,0:02:47.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,他为什么要这样 我真搞不懂\N{\fs90}Why does he do that? I have no idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.54,0:02:48.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,还有谁是芬兰人\N{\fs90}Who else is there, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.53,0:02:49.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,有米卡 萨罗\N{\fs90}Well, there's Mika Salo,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.01,0:02:51.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,米卡 哈基宁  基米 莱科宁\N{\fs90}Mika Häkkinen, Kimi Räikkönen.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.94,0:02:54.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,等等 这些都同一个名字的不同拼法吧\N{\fs90}Hang on, they're just anagrams of the same name, aren't they?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.07,0:02:56.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,下面再说拉力车手\N{\fs90}Then you've got rallying.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.54,0:02:59.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,托米 马基宁  蒂莫 马基宁\N{\fs90}There's Tommi Mäkinen, Timo Mäkinen,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.06,0:03:01.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,尤哈 坎库宁  阿里 瓦塔宁\N{\fs90}Juha Kankkunen, Ari Vatanen.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.51,0:03:03.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,更多的重组词\N{\fs90}More anagrams.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.91,0:03:05.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,坑卡 万科宁\N{\fs90}Kinky Wankinen.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.28,0:03:10.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,曼卡 盘他宁\N{\fs90}Manky Pantiden.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.27,0:03:12.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,真有吗\N{\fs90}Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.40,0:03:14.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,我有些不知所措了\N{\fs90}I'm getting slightly carried away now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.22,0:03:16.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,说真的 我昨晚查了维基\N{\fs90}Seriously, I went on Wikipedia last nigh
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.59,0:03:19.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,想找一些非赛车手的芬兰名人\N{\fs90}to look for famous Finns who aren't racing drivers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.47,0:03:21.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是我列出来的\N{\fs90}Put up the list I found.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.06,0:03:22.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,我还注意到 \N{\fs90}And I noticed something
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.36,0:03:23.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们都是男的\N{\fs90} they're all men.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.94,0:03:25.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,所有都是\N{\fs90}All of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.51,0:03:28.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,有任何有名的芬兰女人吗\N{\fs90}Are there any famous Finnish women?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.56,0:03:31.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,芬兰人民们\N{\fs90}Finnish people?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.47,0:03:34.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们也不知道 说不出来\N{\fs90}Nobody thinks so. They're all...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.49,0:03:35.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,我知道为什么\N{\fs90}I know why, OK?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.97,0:03:39.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,那是因为所有的芬兰女人 在19岁的时候\N{\fs90}It's because all Finnish women, at the age of 19,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.62,0:03:41.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,都会前往英国成为互惠生\N{\fs90}move to England to be au pairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.64,0:03:44.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,这几年我给我的孩子们\N{\fs90}I actually had three Finnish au pairs
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.01,0:03:46.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,找过三个芬兰互惠生\N{\fs90} over the years for my children.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.26,0:03:47.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,-真的吗 -是的 这很有趣\N{\fs90}-Did you? -Yeah. It was always funny.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.03,0:03:50.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,你到希斯罗机场去接你的新互惠生\N{\fs90}You'd go to Heathrow airport to pick up your new au pair,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.56,0:03:52.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且总是一群三十多岁的父亲们\N{\fs90}and there'd always be a row of 30-something
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.99,0:03:55.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,排成一列在门前\N{\fs90} fathers waiting at the gate
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.35,0:03:58.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,等着他们的斯堪的纳维亚互惠生们出来\N{\fs90}for their Scandinavian au pair to come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.77,0:04:01.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,有一年我永远不会忘记\N{\fs90}And there was one year I've never forgotten.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.17,0:04:05.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,有一个壮如驼鹿的人走了出来\N{\fs90}This huge moose lumbered out of the door,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.26,0:04:07.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,我旁边的人看了看他的接机牌然后说\N{\fs90}and the man next to me looked at his piece of paper and went
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.81,0:04:10.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,天啊 饶了我吧\N{\fs90}"Oh, for God's sake!"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.15,0:04:13.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,这可不好\N{\fs90}That's not good.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.72,0:04:19.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我们可以继续节目了吗 -好主意\N{\fs90}-Shall we get on with the show? -Yes, good idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.02,0:04:24.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为今晚 在我们这档汽车节目里\N{\fs90}Because tonight in our television programme about cars...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.53,0:04:26.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,我吃了点切达奶酪\N{\fs90}I eat some cheddar.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.50,0:04:30.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,理查德说他不想吃\N{\fs90}Richard says he doesn't want any.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.00,0:04:33.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,我不想吃奶酪\N{\fs90}I don't want cheese.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.10,0:04:38.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,詹姆斯拿一辆福特GT40和法拉利P3比\N{\fs90}And James compares a Ford GT40 to a Ferrari P3.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.67,0:04:41.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,冲啊\N{\fs90}Avanti!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.55,0:04:44.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,但首先 如果你是在美国收看节目\N{\fs90}But first, if you are watching this in America,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.40,0:04:46.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,你可能会很惊讶的听到\N{\fs90}you may be amazed to hear
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.54,0:04:51.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,福特野马没有在英国正式发售过\N{\fs90}that the Ford Mustang has never been sold, officially, in the UK.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.43,0:04:53.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,但现在不一样了 因为福特决定要将\N{\fs90}Well, until now, because Ford has now decided
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.82,0:04:57.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,最新款的野马在英国发售\N{\fs90}that the latest Mustang will be sold in the UK
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.28,0:05:00.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,配备V8引擎和右座驾驶\N{\fs90}with a V8 engine and right-hand drive.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.55,0:05:03.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,恩 这让我们这位美国同事\N{\fs90}Mm, and this has made our other resident American
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.60,0:05:05.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,非常开心\N{\fs90} very happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.19,0:05:07.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,事实上他过于兴奋了\N{\fs90}He was so excited, in fact,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.29,0:05:09.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,当第一辆右舵野马\N{\fs90}that when the first right-hand-drive Mustang
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.03,0:05:11.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,到达英国伦敦港的时候\N{\fs90}arrived at the docks in the UK,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.58,0:05:14.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,他专程去迎接了\N{\fs90}he was actually there to meet it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.66,0:05:37.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,它随时会来\N{\fs90}It'll be here any minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.07,0:05:51.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,来了 准备好了吗\N{\fs90}That is it. Are we ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.67,0:05:54.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,终于等到了 它落地了\N{\fs90}This is the moment. It's touched down!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.89,0:05:56.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,走起\N{\fs90}Go, go, go!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.56,0:06:06.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,这曲子有点太阴郁了吧\N{\fs90}Look, it's a bit gloomy, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.83,0:06:07.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,不适合作为欢迎曲 \N{\fs90}It's not very welcoming
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.87,0:06:09.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,换首欢快一点的\N{\fs90}Have you got anything more upbeat?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.81,0:06:16.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,算了算了算了\N{\fs90}Forget it! Forget it! Forget it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.51,0:06:17.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,算了吧\N{\fs90}Forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.39,0:06:25.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,我太激动了 快尿出来了\N{\fs90}I'm so excited, my tinkle is fizzing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.13,0:06:33.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦耶\N{\fs90}Oh, yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.00,0:06:41.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,哦 抱歉了\N{\fs90}Oh. Sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.34,0:06:43.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们实在是太没用了\N{\fs90}We really are useless over here.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.66,0:06:46.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以二战的时候才需要你们帮忙\N{\fs90}It's one of the reasons we needed your help in the war.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.50,0:06:51.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,首先 我决定\N{\fs90}I decided that, first of all,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.31,0:06:53.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,要带新野马四处转转\N{\fs90}I'd show the new Mustang around,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.35,0:06:55.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以我直奔伦敦\N{\fs90}so I headed for London...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.70,0:06:57.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,也就是英国的首都\N{\fs90}which is the capital city.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.27,0:07:20.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是伦敦塔桥\N{\fs90}Ah, now, this is Tower Bridge.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.39,0:07:23.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,有趣的是 它非常古老\N{\fs90}Interesting. It's very, very old.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.06,0:07:25.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是它能完全的折叠成一半\N{\fs90}But it folds completely in half
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.52,0:07:28.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,早年间 马车也会从这过\N{\fs90}so that, in the old days, the horses could go through.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.77,0:07:34.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,这里是国会大厦\N{\fs90}Now, that's the Houses of Parliament,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.67,0:07:38.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,里面住着的都是傻瓜\N{\fs90}which are a series of houses in which we keep all our idiots.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.19,0:07:41.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,那个钟 叫大本钟\N{\fs90}That clock thing, that's Big Ben.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.94,0:07:44.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,我知道对你来说不算"大" \N{\fs90}I know it's not what you call big
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.23,0:07:46.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,但不能只叫它"本“啊\N{\fs90}but... but we couldn't just call it Ben.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.77,0:07:50.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是和平纪念碑\N{\fs90}And that is the Cenotaph,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.72,0:07:54.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,用来纪念那些为国捐躯的烈士们\N{\fs90}where we remember those who died fighting for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.55,0:07:57.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,这里要开慢点\N{\fs90}Slowing down a bit here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.76,0:07:59.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,以示尊重\N{\fs90}Show some respect.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.30,0:08:03.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,这个不知道是什么 \N{\fs90}No idea what that is
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.98,0:08:05.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,今天早上还没有呢\N{\fs90} It wasn't here this morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.21,0:08:10.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,那是一个骑自行车的人 你要特别小心\N{\fs90}A cyclist, you want to be careful of those.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.08,0:08:12.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,那种生物特别暴躁\N{\fs90}Small but very angry creatures.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.18,0:08:16.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,那是一支军队\N{\fs90}That's the army.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.63,0:08:18.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,当年就是他们朝白宫开了枪\N{\fs90}They're the ones who shot at your White House.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.95,0:08:20.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,真不好意思\N{\fs90}Sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.11,0:08:23.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,逛完所有景点之后\N{\fs90}Having seen all of the sights,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.95,0:08:26.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们开出了城\N{\fs90}we headed out of town
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.06,0:08:28.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,我终于可以放开手脚了\N{\fs90}so I could do this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.97,0:08:33.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,就是这样\N{\fs90}There it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.72,0:08:35.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,这就是让英国\N{\fs90}That is the soundtrack
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.33,0:08:38.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,朝思暮想了51年的声浪\N{\fs90}that Britain has been missing for 51 years -
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.16,0:08:40.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,真正的美国V8肌肉车\N{\fs90}real American V8 muscle.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.56,0:08:48.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,大洋彼岸的我们不造这样的车\N{\fs90}We just don't make cars like this on our side of the pond.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.30,0:08:51.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,所有那些懒惰而又坚定的扭矩\N{\fs90}All that lazy-but-determined torque.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.07,0:08:55.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,在任何档位和速度下都能爆发\N{\fs90}Squeeze the throttle in any gear at any speed...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.11,0:08:59.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,它的畅销是必然的\N{\fs90}...and there's an inevitability to the way it moves off.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.12,0:09:00.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,这就像和太阳系掰手腕\N{\fs90}It's like arm wrestling a solar system
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.92,0:09:02.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,你必输无疑\N{\fs90}you're gonna lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.44,0:09:13.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,感觉好奇怪\N{\fs90}It is weird...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.95,0:09:16.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,坐在右边开野马\N{\fs90}driving a Mustang from this side.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.23,0:09:19.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,就好像在结婚五十年之后\N{\fs90}It's like suddenly changing your mind after
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.19,0:09:22.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,突然换到床的另一边睡一样\N{\fs90}50 years of marriage and sleeping on the other side of the bed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.80,0:09:26.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且开着一辆仅售37000英镑\N{\fs90}It's also weird driving a car with a big V8,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.52,0:09:28.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,巨大的V8引擎 倒车影像\N{\fs90}reversing camera, air-conditioned seats,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.99,0:09:30.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,座椅通风\N{\fs90}rain-sensing wipers
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.45,0:09:33.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,以及感应雨刷的车也很奇怪\N{\fs90} that you can buy for £37,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.43,0:09:37.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是宝马M4一半的价钱 一半\N{\fs90}That's half of what you'd pay for a BMW M4. Half.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.00,0:09:42.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,这时我们已经完全进入了市郊\N{\fs90}Once we were in the countryside proper,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.47,0:09:45.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,继续我们的观光之旅\N{\fs90}I continued my sightseeing tour.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.27,0:09:49.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,看 我把你的标志画在了小山坡上\N{\fs90}Look, I've drawn your badge on a hill.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.11,0:09:57.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,那个是杰里米画的\N{\fs90}Jeremy did that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.95,0:10:03.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,抱歉啦\N{\fs90}Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.49,0:10:08.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,最终我们到达了巨石阵\N{\fs90}Eventually, we arrived at Stonehenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.63,0:10:13.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,看呐 你会很吃惊地发现\N{\fs90}That, you'll be amazed to learn,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.48,0:10:16.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是个古代的日历\N{\fs90}is an ancient calendar.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.20,0:10:19.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,或者是块表 或者是教堂\N{\fs90}Or a clock. Or a church.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.90,0:10:22.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,我的英国一日游\N{\fs90}My tour of Britain was then interrupted
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.38,0:10:24.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,被一位不速之客打断了\N{\fs90}by an unwelcome arrival.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.53,0:10:28.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,你来干什么\N{\fs90}What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.06,0:10:31.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,我是来提醒你\N{\fs90}Well, I have come to remind you -
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.52,0:10:32.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为你显然已经忘了\N{\fs90}cos you've obviously forgotten,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.82,0:10:34.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,也因为你满脑子浆糊\N{\fs90}cos you're too giddy -
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.29,0:10:37.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们在英国不需要野马\N{\fs90}that we have no need for the Mustang in Britain.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.53,0:10:39.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果我们想买一辆\N{\fs90}Because if you want to spend,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.80,0:10:42.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,价格在3万到3万5英镑 讲究速度的福特\N{\fs90}what, £30,000-£35,000 on a fast Ford,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.81,0:10:44.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,买福克斯RS啊 \N{\fs90}you'd buy a Focus RS
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.61,0:10:46.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,再合适不过了\N{\fs90} cos that was designed for here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.45,0:10:49.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,不 以前在英国是只好买那个\N{\fs90}No, you'd settle for that in the UK
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.15,0:10:51.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为买不到野马 但现在不同\N{\fs90}because you couldn't buy this, but now you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.55,0:10:52.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,就是这样\N{\fs90}That is the point.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.70,0:10:55.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,你会穿皮套裤吗\N{\fs90}Would you wear chaps?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.14,0:10:57.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,不会 因为我们有正经的裤子\N{\fs90}No, because we have trousers.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.45,0:10:58.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,你会穿牛仔靴 \N{\fs90}What about cowboy...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.45,0:10:59.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,噢你已经穿上了\N{\fs90}Oh, you are. Cowboy boots.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.85,0:11:01.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,很恰当啊 我在迎接它\N{\fs90}Well, it's appropriate. I'm welcoming...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.30,0:11:03.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,听着 我不是喜欢美国的一切 \N{\fs90}Listen, I don't want everything from America
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.53,0:11:04.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,我只是爱野马\N{\fs90} I just want the Mustang.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.79,0:11:05.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,-蠢货 -不是 美国\N{\fs90}-Stupid. -No, America--
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.09,0:11:07.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,野马并不适合这里\N{\fs90}It wasn't designed for here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.82,0:11:10.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,-你会戴毡帽吗 -不会\N{\fs90}-Would you wear a Stetson? -Well, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.31,0:11:12.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,天太冷了 我戴顶毡帽吧\N{\fs90}"It's cold out, I'll wear a Stetson."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.09,0:11:13.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,不 你会戴毛绒帽\N{\fs90}No! You wear a bobble hat.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.10,0:11:15.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,这辆车就是毛绒帽\N{\fs90}That's a bobble hat.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.80,0:11:17.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,对了 等一下\N{\fs90}Oh! No, hang on.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.17,0:11:20.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我刚想起来 -怎么了\N{\fs90}-I've just realised. -What?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.83,0:11:23.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,哎 我不想再跟你说话了\N{\fs90}Erm... I-I don't want to talk to you any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.28,0:11:42.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,总而言之\N{\fs90}Anyway...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.96,0:11:46.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,总之 我们一会儿再继续\N{\fs90}Anyway, we shall pick that up later on.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.95,0:11:49.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,但现在是时候降档\N{\fs90}But right now it's time to drop it a cog
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.40,0:11:52.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,左拐进入唠嗑街了\N{\fs90}and hook a left into Conversation Street.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.88,0:12:03.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,-严肃点 -这很正经的\N{\fs90}-Serious.- It's serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.49,0:12:05.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,这就是很正经的东西\N{\fs90}It is serious stuff, this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.37,0:12:08.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在听好了 我们在英国经常听说\N{\fs90}Now, look, in Britain we are always being told
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.93,0:12:11.48,字幕,,0,0,0,,北欧人开车很厉害\N{\fs90}that the Scandinavians are brilliant at driving,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.50,0:12:13.18,字幕,,0,0,0,,这也难怪 \N{\fs90}and that's because they would be
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.20,0:12:15.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为他们经常会遇到积雪路面\N{\fs90}because they have to deal with all that snow.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.61,0:12:19.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们厉害的原因就是因为经常撞车\N{\fs90}Mm, they're brilliant because what they do most of all is crash.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.18,0:12:21.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,你说的太对了 事实证明\N{\fs90}Well, you're absolutely right, as it turns out,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.36,0:12:23.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,我拿到了一些有意思的数据\N{\fs90}cos I've got some interesting statistics here. Erm...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.55,0:12:28.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,在英国 车祸的死亡率为1.2%\N{\fs90}In Britain, 1.2% of accidents result in fatalities.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.54,0:12:31.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,而在芬兰 恐怕是5.1%\N{\fs90}Here, I'm afraid, it's 5.1%.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.15,0:12:33.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,嗯 不光是芬兰人\N{\fs90}Yeah, and it's not just the Finns, either,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.17,0:12:34.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,我这么说有点莽撞\N{\fs90}if I may be so bold.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.95,0:12:37.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们的资深国际制片人\N{\fs90}Our Senior International Producer -
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.71,0:12:38.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,这就是他的职位\N{\fs90}that's his job title -
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.93,0:12:40.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,前几天来到了芬兰\N{\fs90}came over to Finland the other day,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.01,0:12:43.19,字幕,,0,0,0,,在机场租了辆宝马\N{\fs90}rented himself a BMW at the airport -
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.22,0:12:45.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,不是福特也不是欧宝 而是宝马\N{\fs90}not a Ford or an Opel,you'll note, a BMW -
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.49,0:12:47.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,在他前往这里的时候\N{\fs90}and on his way to the location here,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.55,0:12:48.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,发生了这样一幕\N{\fs90}this happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.86,0:12:51.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,他确实翻车了\N{\fs90}He did! He did!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.43,0:12:53.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,我说他曾是资深国际制片人\N{\fs90}When I say he's our Senior International Producer,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.97,0:12:56.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在已经降级为初级国际制片人了\N{\fs90}he's now our Junior International Producer.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.23,0:12:58.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我们初级本地制片人 -嗯\N{\fs90}-Our Junior Local Producer.-Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.90,0:13:01.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,非常本地 准确的说是文具柜\N{\fs90}Very local. Specifically,the stationery cupboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.67,0:13:04.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,-他能胜任 -他也只能负责这个了\N{\fs90}-He can produce that.-That's all he's in charge of.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.31,0:13:05.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,他是怎么开翻的\N{\fs90}How did he do that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.92,0:13:07.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,问题是 我不明白\N{\fs90}The thing is, what I don't understand is
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.54,0:13:09.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,芬兰人为什么要开那么快\N{\fs90} how the Finns manage to go fast enough
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.68,0:13:11.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,还以各种方式撞车\N{\fs90}to have a crash of any sort at all,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.75,0:13:15.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为这里的超速罚金相当高\N{\fs90}because the speeding fines here are insane.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.33,0:13:16.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,我说的是真的\N{\fs90}They're means tested,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.79,0:13:18.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,前一阵有人在限速48km/h\N{\fs90}which means a guy here recently
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.95,0:13:21.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,的地方开到了78km/h\N{\fs90}was caught doing 49mph through a 30 zone
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.17,0:13:26.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,结果他被罚了11.2万欧元\N{\fs90}and he was fined 112,000 euros.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.53,0:13:28.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,这只是张超速罚单啊\N{\fs90}That's a speeding fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.46,0:13:30.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,芬兰真的罚得这么狠吗\N{\fs90}Are they really that high in Finland?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.74,0:13:32.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,真的假的\N{\fs90}They are?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.57,0:13:33.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,11万\N{\fs90}A hundred and twelve...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.66,0:13:35.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,11万2千\N{\fs90}112,000.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.24,0:13:36.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,想象一下他收到罚单时的表情 \N{\fs90}-Imagine getting that in the post!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.87,0:13:37.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,有意思的是\N{\fs90}Well, it's interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.99,0:13:41.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,实际上 芬兰首相最近说\N{\fs90}Actually, there was a Finnish minister recently said
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.07,0:13:43.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,政府很需要那些超速罚单\N{\fs90}that the government needs those speeding fines
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.61,0:13:45.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,来平衡那些负债\N{\fs90}to balance the books,they said.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.95,0:13:49.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们甚至说 超速有利于国家经济发展\N{\fs90}They actually said, "Speeding is good for the country."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.06,0:13:51.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,这其实就是\N{\fs90}That is actually what...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.62,0:13:53.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,对于每个国家来说都是如此\N{\fs90}Because it is. Every country.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.59,0:13:56.52,字幕,,0,0,0,,嗯 我们也该采纳这点\N{\fs90}Right. We should adopt that.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.82,0:13:59.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,-超速好处大大的 -是你们的社会责任\N{\fs90}-Speeding is good for you.-It's your social duty.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.69,0:14:01.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,-咱们再聊会啊 -哦 好啊\N{\fs90}-A bit more conversation for you.-Oh, good!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.36,0:14:06.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,我觉得除了劳斯莱斯\N{\fs90}I think, with the exception of Rolls-Royce,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.10,0:14:10.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,现在沃尔沃的内饰做的是最好的\N{\fs90}Volvo now make the best car interiors of anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.98,0:14:13.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们做得确实非常出色\N{\fs90}They do. They're very, very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.81,0:14:15.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,不得不说 我同意\N{\fs90}I don't like to,but I agree with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.84,0:14:18.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,我前段时间开过新款S90 \N{\fs90}because I went in the new S90 the other day
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.11,0:14:19.71,字幕,,0,0,0,, 内饰真的非常棒\N{\fs90}and the interior is superb.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.73,0:14:22.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我们这里有张图 -对 就是这款\N{\fs90}-We've got a picture of it here.-Yes, that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.12,0:14:23.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们用的都是淡色\N{\fs90}They use pale colours.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.37,0:14:25.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,座椅 地毯 \N{\fs90}They've got pale-coloured seats, pale-coloured carpets
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.18,0:14:26.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,木饰条都是淡色的\N{\fs90}pale wood,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.04,0:14:28.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,给人感觉明亮 通透且宽敞\N{\fs90}and that makes it feel light and airy and spacious.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.89,0:14:31.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,唯一的问题是 在这样的车里\N{\fs90}The only problem is that in one of those
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.56,0:14:35.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,你没法吃梦龙巧克力冰淇淋\N{\fs90}you couldn't enjoy a chocolate Magnum ice cream.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.05,0:14:37.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,无所谓 我不吃冰淇淋\N{\fs90}It's all right,I don't eat ice cream.
