Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.73,0:46:20.33,字幕,,0,0,0,,他就在这项著名的高强度24小时耐力赛中\N{\fs90}he had won the famous and gruelling 24-hour race
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.40,0:46:22.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,收获了三连冠\N{\fs90}three times on the trot.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.83,0:46:26.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是 公司当时却正面临着严重财政困难\N{\fs90}However, the company was in deep financial difficulty,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.01,0:46:30.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以当福特提出要全盘收购的时候\N{\fs90}so when Ford offered to buy the entire business,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:30.21,0:46:32.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,恩佐同意了\N{\fs90}Enzo agreed.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.05,0:46:37.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,起初 一切都很顺利\N{\fs90}At first, all went well.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.22,0:46:41.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,恩佐法拉利和福特公司的老大 亨利福特二世\N{\fs90}Enzo Ferrari and the head of Ford, Henry Ford II,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.69,0:46:45.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,很快就定下了1600万美金的价格\N{\fs90}quickly settled on a price of $16 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.99,0:46:49.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,1963年5月21日\N{\fs90}And on May 21st 1963,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.13,0:46:54.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,福特的管理层抵达马拉内罗来签署合同\N{\fs90}Ford executives arrived in Maranello to sign the deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.23,0:46:56.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,福特带了一大帮的精英律师\N{\fs90}Ford turned up with an army of suits.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.67,0:46:58.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,而恩佐法拉利对面而坐\N{\fs90}Enzo Ferrari sat opposite them
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.60,0:47:00.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,身旁却只是镇上的小律师\N{\fs90}with just the local town lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.97,0:47:02.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们检查了合同 一切看似没有问题\N{\fs90}They read the contract and all seemed well,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:02.94,0:47:05.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,但突然间 法拉利的目光停了下来\N{\fs90}but then, suddenly, Ferrari stopped
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.08,0:47:08.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后他拿出了那支有名的灌着紫色墨水的钢笔\N{\fs90}and he took out his famous fountain pen full of purple ink,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.11,0:47:11.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,从我手上的这份副本上大家可以看到\N{\fs90}and as you can see from this accurate copy I have here,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.35,0:47:13.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,他在这画了一个大大的感叹号并写道\N{\fs90}he drew a big exclamation mark and he wrote,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.95,0:47:16.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,不 这条不行\N{\fs90}"No, that's no good!"
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.36,0:47:17.65,字幕,,0,0,0,,是什么让他这么生气呢 \N{\fs90}Now, what had angered him?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:17.70,0:47:19.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,呐 是这里的这个条款\N{\fs90} Well, it was this clause here.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.42,0:47:22.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,是这样 恩佐法拉利想要保留\N{\fs90}You see, Enzo Ferrari wanted to retain control
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.33,0:47:24.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,对于赛车部门的控制权\N{\fs90}of the motorsport side of his business,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.53,0:47:29.27,字幕,,0,0,0,,但这个条款却将它给了福特\N{\fs90}but this bit effectively handed control to Ford.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.33,0:47:32.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,在一通意语的喋喋谩骂之后\N{\fs90}There followed a tirade of abuse in Italian,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.74,0:47:34.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,恩佐法拉利跟他的律师说了句 \N{\fs90}after which, Enzo said to his lawyer
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.72,0:47:35.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,到饭点了\N{\fs90}"Let's go and eat."
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.73,0:47:37.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后就在福特管理层的一片错愕当中\N{\fs90}Then they got up and they simply walked out
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.95,0:47:39.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,起身离去\N{\fs90} on the stunned Ford executives.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.91,0:47:41.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,这事就这么黄了\N{\fs90}That was that.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.49,0:47:43.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,这一切都成了无用功\N{\fs90}All of this for nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.98,0:47:47.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,回到底特律 亨利福特二世\N{\fs90}Back in Detroit, Henry Ford II,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.02,0:47:49.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,怒不可遏\N{\fs90}apoplectic with rage,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.82,0:47:52.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,召集了他的将领向他们下达了指令\N{\fs90}gathered his lieutenants and issued the order:
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.76,0:47:56.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,给我造一辆能在勒芒上碾压法拉利的车\N{\fs90}"Build me a car that will crush Ferrari at Le Mans."
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.96,0:48:02.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,想要在欧洲地盘上战胜法拉利\N{\fs90}To beat Ferrari on European soil,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.30,0:48:04.60,字幕,,0,0,0,,福特需要来自欧洲的专家\N{\fs90}Ford needed European expertise,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.67,0:48:07.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,所以他雇了一家小型的英国赛车厂\N{\fs90}so he hired a small British motorsport company
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.07,0:48:10.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,就在这栋建筑里生火搭灶\N{\fs90}that set up shop here, in this very building,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.61,0:48:14.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,这里是离伦敦不远的斯劳工业区\N{\fs90}on an industrial estate in Slough, just outside London.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.65,0:48:18.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,而他们所面临的挑战是巨大的\N{\fs90}And the challenges they faced were enormous.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.32,0:48:22.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们需要造一辆能够跑到320公里以上的车\N{\fs90}They had to build a car that would race at over 200mph,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.52,0:48:24.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,这本身就已经前无古人了\N{\fs90}which was something that had never been done before,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.32,0:48:28.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且还要在勒芒耐力赛中坚持24个小时\N{\fs90}and it had to be reliable for the 24 hours of the Le Mans race -
Dialogue: 0,0:48:28.76,0:48:32.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,这其中将经历约9000次换挡\N{\fs90}a race in which you changed gear 9,000 times
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.33,0:48:35.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,和4800多公里的全速行驶\N{\fs90}and drove flat out for 3,000 miles.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.00,0:48:38.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,更要命的是 \N{\fs90}And, as if that wasn't bad enough
Dialogue: 0,0:48:38.12,0:48:40.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们只有十个月的时间\N{\fs90} they only had ten months to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.04,0:48:48.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,在这样疯狂的时间表下\N{\fs90}Out of that insane timetable emerged this.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:50.55,0:48:52.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,福特GT诞生了\N{\fs90}The Ford GT.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.70,0:48:54.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,凭借其光滑的车身\N{\fs90}Thanks to its sleek shape
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.09,0:48:56.89,字幕,,0,0,0,,和仅仅100公分的车身高度\N{\fs90} and the body that stood just 40-inches tall,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.96,0:49:00.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,它能如导弹般切割空气\N{\fs90}it promised to cut through the air like a missile.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.89,0:49:02.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,再加上一台4.2升的V8发动机\N{\fs90}Add a 4.2L V8,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.03,0:49:08.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,320公里的极速看似唾手可得\N{\fs90}and the magic target of 200mph seemed in the bag.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.27,0:49:09.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,问题是 \N{\fs90}The trouble is
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.37,0:49:13.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,赛车这东西 在上赛道之前\N{\fs90}a racing car is just a collection of hopes and dreams
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.14,0:49:15.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,一切都是纸上谈兵\N{\fs90}until it gets on the track.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.87,0:49:18.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,福特为此吸取了惨痛的教训\N{\fs90}And that's something that Ford learned in a very brutal way
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.71,0:49:23.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,在他们第一次在勒芒测试GT40的时候\N{\fs90}when they took the GT40 to test at Le Mans for the first time.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:25.05,0:49:27.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,第一次勒芒练习赛拉开了帷幕\N{\fs90}And so to the first Le Mans practice session.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.05,0:49:32.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,第一次亮相 重新命名的GT40很快\N{\fs90}On its first outing, the renamed GT40 was fast,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.69,0:49:35.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,但也惊人的不稳定\N{\fs90}but it was also terrifyingly unstable,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:35.49,0:49:38.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,在直道上后轮都会打滑\N{\fs90}spinning its wheels on the straights.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.56,0:49:40.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,我说的可不是在你刚刚出发的时候\N{\fs90}I'm not talking about when you set off,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:40.63,0:49:44.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,而是在时速270km/h的时候打滑\N{\fs90}I mean it was happening at 170mph!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.81,0:49:50.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,问题不是出在空气动力学上就是出在悬挂上\N{\fs90}Now, the problem was either aerodynamics or suspension,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.17,0:49:51.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,但他们永远也没机会弄明白\N{\fs90}but they never found out,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.58,0:49:56.92,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为那天晚些时候 那辆车以257公里的时速撞毁了\N{\fs90}because, later that day, the car crashed at 160mph.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.98,0:49:59.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,没关系 他们当然还有一辆备用车\N{\fs90}Well, that was OK. They had a spare one, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:59.82,0:50:02.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,第二天 备用车也撞了\N{\fs90}The next day, that crashed as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.42,0:50:05.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,这时候据勒芒只有两个月了\N{\fs90}Le Mans was just two months away.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.03,0:50:09.35,字幕,,0,0,0,,历经千难万险 \N{\fs90}Against all odds
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.38,0:50:14.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,福特险险赶上了1964年的大赛\N{\fs90} Ford got their act together in time for the 1964 race.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.93,0:50:17.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们终于迎来了勒芒24小时耐力赛\N{\fs90}The Le Mans 24 Hour Race at last,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.07,0:50:20.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,和三辆崭新的福特GT\N{\fs90}and three gleaming Ford GTs are present.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.74,0:50:22.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是在比赛中\N{\fs90}But during the race itself,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.84,0:50:26.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,三辆车不是抛锚就是起火\N{\fs90}all the cars broke down or caught fire,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.38,0:50:28.38,字幕,,0,0,0,,这使得他们憎恨的对手法拉利\N{\fs90}leaving bitter rivals Ferrari
Dialogue: 0,0:50:28.45,0:50:32.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,再一次囊括了前三名\N{\fs90}to take another one-two-three victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.59,0:50:36.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,底特律那边 \N{\fs90}In Detroit
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.63,0:50:39.42,字幕,,0,0,0,,亨利福特决定他们明年会回来\N{\fs90}Henry Ford decreed that they would be back next year
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.49,0:50:41.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,再战法拉利\N{\fs90}to take on Ferrari again.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.69,0:50:43.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,而领导这场战斗的人选\N{\fs90}And to head up the campaign,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:43.60,0:50:46.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,福特则想到了美国的赛车英雄\N{\fs90}he turned to an American motorsport hero.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.00,0:50:50.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,我叫卡罗尔谢尔比 我为性能车代言\N{\fs90}My name's Carroll Shelby and performance is my business.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.30,0:50:53.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,谢尔比原先是德州的一名养鸡户\N{\fs90}Shelby was a former chicken farmer from Texas
Dialogue: 0,0:50:53.47,0:50:56.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,平日里他需要服用硝化甘油来缓解他的心绞痛\N{\fs90}who took nitroglycerin pills to keep his heart going.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.98,0:50:59.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,但他作为车手和车队老板\N{\fs90}But he'd also racked up countless victories
Dialogue: 0,0:50:59.41,0:51:01.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,则赢下了无数的胜利\N{\fs90}as a driver and team owner.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.95,0:51:04.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,面对把GT40调教成冠军之车的任务\N{\fs90}Given the task of turning the GT40 into a winner,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:04.92,0:51:07.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,他派出了自己的王牌干将\N{\fs90}he put his top man on the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:07.29,0:51:08.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,接下来 您将看到的是肯迈尔斯\N{\fs90}Coming up is Ken Miles,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.85,0:51:12.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,全美最棒的跑车车手之一\N{\fs90}one of the best sport-car drivers in America.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:12.49,0:51:15.82,字幕,,0,0,0,,迈尔斯是一名来自伯明翰的\N{\fs90}Miles was a former Second World War tank commander
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.84,0:51:17.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,前二战坦克指挥官\N{\fs90} from Birmingham -
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.22,0:51:19.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,英国伯明翰 不是亚拉巴马那个\N{\fs90}the one in England, not Alabama.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.93,0:51:21.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,他以心直口快\N{\fs90}He was renowned for speaking his mind
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.90,0:51:25.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,和善于调教赛车出名\N{\fs90}and developing racing cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.07,0:51:26.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,迈尔斯试了试这车\N{\fs90}Miles took the car for a shakedown.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.84,0:51:30.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,下车后 他对谢尔比和福特的高层说\N{\fs90}Then he got out and he told Shelby and the Ford executives,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.14,0:51:31.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,这什么破车\N{\fs90}"It's bloody awful!"
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.81,0:51:33.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,然后他开始了工作\N{\fs90}Then he got to work,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.55,0:51:36.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,改进刹车 引擎\N{\fs90}improving the brakes, the engine,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:36.08,0:51:38.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,空气动力学设计 操控\N{\fs90}the aerodynamics, the handling,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.12,0:51:43.12,字幕,,0,0,0,,还有驯化这车高速时令人惊悚的不稳定性\N{\fs90}and taming the car's terrifying high-speed instability.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.19,0:51:46.22,字幕,,0,0,0,,不过 尽管他和他的团队服用安非他命\N{\fs90}However, and even though he and his team took amphetamine
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.29,0:51:48.09,字幕,,0,0,0,,来使自己可以通宵工作\N{\fs90}so that they could stay awake all night,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.16,0:51:51.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,但研发一台能够参加勒芒的赛车\N{\fs90}there simply wasn't time to develop the car properly
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.46,0:51:52.88,字幕,,0,0,0,,时间依然不够\N{\fs90}for Le Mans.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.20,0:51:55.53,字幕,,0,0,0,,虽然GT40的车速更快了\N{\fs90}The GT40 may have been faster,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:55.60,0:51:57.67,字幕,,0,0,0,,但它们却依然弱不禁风\N{\fs90}but it was still fragile.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.74,0:51:59.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,在1965年的比赛中\N{\fs90}At the 1965 race,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.60,0:52:02.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,有六辆车参赛 却无一完赛\N{\fs90}six cars started, none finished,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.17,0:52:06.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,而意大利人又一次羞辱了福特\N{\fs90}and the Italians humiliated Ford once again.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.15,0:52:11.08,字幕,,0,0,0,,数以百万的银子花了\N{\fs90}So, untold millions of dollars had been spent
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.15,0:52:14.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,算上从这栋建筑里走出来的第一辆GT40\N{\fs90}since the first GT40 emerged from this building here,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.75,0:52:18.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,居然没有任何一辆能够顺利完赛\N{\fs90}and yet not one car had even finished the race.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.92,0:52:20.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,福特现在面临一个艰难的选择\N{\fs90}So Ford now faced a difficult choice -
Dialogue: 0,0:52:20.69,0:52:23.07,字幕,,0,0,0,,他要不向法拉利认输 \N{\fs90}he could throw in the towel against Ferrari
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.13,0:52:24.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,要不就得继续战斗\N{\fs90}or he could fight on.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.80,0:52:27.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,而他选择给他的勒芒团队\N{\fs90}What he actually did was he had some business cards printed,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:28.03,0:52:30.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,都打印了名片\N{\fs90}and he distributed them to his Le Mans team.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:30.60,0:52:33.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,名片上写着 你最好得赢\N{\fs90}And on the cards it said, "You'd better win."
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.59,0:52:35.34,字幕,,0,0,0,,于是 一年之后\N{\fs90}And so, a year later,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.41,0:52:38.04,字幕,,0,0,0,,美国汽车巨头重回勒芒\N{\fs90}the American giant returned to Le Mans
Dialogue: 0,0:52:38.11,0:52:41.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,并将希望寄托在这辆车身上\N{\fs90}with its hopes resting on this.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.69,0:52:51.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,观众朋友们\N{\fs90}OK, viewers,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.22,0:52:56.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是我死前必开的历史性赛车清单上排名第二的\N{\fs90}this is historic-race-car bucket-list moment number two,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.29,0:52:59.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为这是一辆真正参加过\N{\fs90}because this is an actual GT40
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.10,0:53:02.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,1966年勒芒比赛的GT40\N{\fs90}that competed at Le Mans in 1966.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:05.24,0:53:08.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,好了 别胡来 这车可是值1500万英镑\N{\fs90}All right, don't go mad, May, it's worth 15-million quid.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.01,0:53:12.61,字幕,,0,0,0,,管他呢 让引擎轰鸣起来吧\N{\fs90}Sod it! Let's make some noise!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.08,0:53:20.02,字幕,,0,0,0,,爽\N{\fs90}Oh, yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.72,0:53:24.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,在这辆新的GT40身上\N{\fs90}In this new GT40,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.39,0:53:28.29,字幕,,0,0,0,,肯迈尔斯跑了上千小时的测试\N{\fs90}Ken Miles had racked up thousands of test hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.36,0:53:31.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,使这辆车终于稳定下来\N{\fs90}Now the car was no longer horribly unstable,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:31.90,0:53:36.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,而是在338公里的时速下也稳如磐石\N{\fs90}but would sit rocksteady at 210mph.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.30,0:53:37.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且伯明翰的坦克指挥官\N{\fs90}And the Brummie tank commander
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.94,0:53:41.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,有福特庞大的研发部门做后盾\N{\fs90} had the backing of Ford's huge R&D department,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:41.31,0:53:44.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,去改善这辆车极其糟糕的可靠性\N{\fs90}who tackled the car's appalling reliability.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.24,0:53:48.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,这车的刹车不会再在直道末端\N{\fs90}The brakes no longer went into thermal shock
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.98,0:53:51.32,字幕,,0,0,0,,出现热衰减\N{\fs90}at the end of the long straight.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.38,0:53:55.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,引擎和变速箱也在电脑控制的试验台上进行了测试\N{\fs90}The engine and transmission were run on a computerised test rig
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.32,0:53:59.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,模拟了整个勒芒24小时耐力赛的过程\N{\fs90}that simulated the whole of the 24-Hour Le Mans race.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.46,0:54:02.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,今天 这是F1测试的标配\N{\fs90}Now, that's standard practice in Formula One today,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:02.09,0:54:05.76,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是在1966年 这就是妖术啊\N{\fs90}but in 1966 that was witchcraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.77,0:54:10.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,这些小伙子们还真没含糊\N{\fs90}They weren't mucking about, these blokes.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.77,0:54:13.03,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们的对手也没含糊\N{\fs90}But neither were the opposition.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.47,0:54:16.68,字幕,,0,0,0,,在意大利这边 面对新出现的对手\N{\fs90}Over in Italy, in response to the new threat,
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.74,0:54:19.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,法拉利的回应是这辆车\N{\fs90}Ferrari produced this.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.58,0:54:30.25,字幕,,0,0,0,,这辆代号P3的车 看上去和GT40一样光滑\N{\fs90}Called the P3, it looked as sleek as a GT40.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.32,0:54:35.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,而其95公分的车身高度 则比福特还低\N{\fs90}And at just 37.4 inches tall, it was even lower.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:39.80,0:54:41.73,字幕,,0,0,0,,冲啊\N{\fs90}Avanti!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:44.70,0:54:47.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,喔 亲娘啊\N{\fs90}Whoo! Holy mother!
Dialogue: 0,0:54:47.07,0:54:50.41,字幕,,0,0,0,,我最好在这条狭窄的道路上小心点\N{\fs90}I best be a little bit careful on this narrow road.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.47,0:54:53.21,字幕,,0,0,0,,它可是值2千万英镑\N{\fs90}It's worth £20 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.18,0:55:00.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,GT40拥有高达338公里每小时的最高时速\N{\fs90}Where the GT40 boasted a top speed of over 210mph,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:00.75,0:55:03.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,而P3最快只能开305公里每小时\N{\fs90}the P3 maxed out at just 190.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:04.02,0:55:06.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,但恩佐法拉利为了其他方面的优势\N{\fs90}But Enzo Ferrari was willing to trade
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.81,0:55:10.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,愿意放弃绝对的速度\N{\fs90} outright speed for gains elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.40,0:55:13.87,字幕,,0,0,0,,这辆车更轻 更灵活\N{\fs90}The Ferrari was lighter, it was more agile.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.93,0:55:17.30,字幕,,0,0,0,,法拉利认为它在弯道可以抹平速度上的差距\N{\fs90}Ferrari reckoned he could make up the difference in the bends,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.37,0:55:20.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,而且还不用经常进站加油\N{\fs90}and he wouldn't have to stop so often for fuel.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.34,0:55:25.84,字幕,,0,0,0,,一场大卫与歌利亚的战争就要打响\N{\fs90}A David and Goliath battle was looming.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.91,0:55:31.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,在1966年的勒芒比赛上 福特带来了一支大军\N{\fs90}At the 1966 Le Mans race, Ford arrived with an armada -
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.52,0:55:34.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,8辆车 20吨的零件\N{\fs90}eight cars, 20 tonnes of spares,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.82,0:55:37.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,一队的世界级车手\N{\fs90}and a squad of world-class drivers,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.22,0:55:39.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,其中包括肯迈尔斯本人\N{\fs90}including Ken Miles himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.86,0:55:44.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,相比之下 法拉利只带了三辆P3\N{\fs90}In comparison, Ferrari turned up with just a trio of P3s,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.33,0:55:46.23,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是恩佐手中也有一张王牌\N{\fs90}but Enzo had an ace up his sleeve -
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.30,0:55:49.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,当时毫无争议的世界最快车手\N{\fs90}the undisputed fastest driver on the planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.03,0:55:54.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,F1世界冠军约翰苏提斯\N{\fs90}Formula One World Champion John Surtees.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.61,0:55:57.01,字幕,,0,0,0,,他走过来对我说 约翰 \N{\fs90}He came to me and said, "John...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.55,0:56:00.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们必须要战胜福特 去击败他们\N{\fs90}we've got to beat the Fords. Go out and do it."
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.01,0:56:02.58,字幕,,0,0,0,,我目前认为只有一种策略能成功\N{\fs90}I thought there was only one tactic -
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.65,0:56:06.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,让至少一辆车来当野兔\N{\fs90}to have at least one car be the hare.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.35,0:56:10.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,我说 听着 我不介意来当那个野兔\N{\fs90}I said, "Look, I don't mind being the hare."
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.79,0:56:12.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,旗子一落下\N{\fs90}"The moment that flag goes down,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:12.66,0:56:14.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们需要有车能撒丫子就跑\N{\fs90}we need to be - bang - off,"
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.66,0:56:19.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,试图引诱福特车手冒险追击\N{\fs90}tempting the Ford drivers to perhaps overdrive a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.53,0:56:22.47,字幕,,0,0,0,,如果能够让他们超负荷驾驶的时间足够长\N{\fs90}If one could push them hard enough for long enough,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:22.53,0:56:24.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们就自然更有可能\N{\fs90}then there is more likelihood, obviously
Dialogue: 0,0:56:24.98,0:56:27.44,字幕,,0,0,0,,把车开坏\N{\fs90}of being able to break them.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:27.81,0:56:29.51,字幕,,0,0,0,,计划订好了\N{\fs90}The plan was set.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.57,0:56:33.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是 就在开赛前 一切都变了\N{\fs90}But, as zero hour approached, everything unravelled.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:33.88,0:56:35.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,就在开赛前不久 \N{\fs90}Shortly before the race
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.44,0:56:37.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们得知他将不会参赛\N{\fs90} we learned that he wasn't going to drive,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.12,0:56:38.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们就此事询问了他\N{\fs90}and we asked him about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.92,0:56:42.62,字幕,,0,0,0,,是的 不幸被言中 我今天不会参赛了\N{\fs90}Yes, unfortunately you've heard correct. I won't be driving.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.69,0:56:44.69,字幕,,0,0,0,,这是为什么呢\N{\fs90}What is the reason?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.82,0:56:47.83,字幕,,0,0,0,,我想现阶段最恰当的表述\N{\fs90}Well, I suppose it's best summed up at this stage
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.86,0:56:50.36,字幕,,0,0,0,,就是 政治原因\N{\fs90}by saying "political reasons."
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.43,0:56:52.70,字幕,,0,0,0,,原因在于法拉利的车队经理\N{\fs90}The problem was that the Ferrari team manager
Dialogue: 0,0:56:52.83,0:56:55.10,字幕,,0,0,0,,自己玩了个政治手段\N{\fs90}was playing his own political game.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.17,0:56:57.57,字幕,,0,0,0,,他对于苏提斯不怎么感冒\N{\fs90}He had no particular liking for Surtees,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.64,0:56:59.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,并且提名另一位车车手\N{\fs90}and he nominated another driver
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.27,0:57:02.31,字幕,,0,0,0,,去跑第一棒 去当野兔\N{\fs90}to go out and start the race, to be the hare,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.37,0:57:07.95,字幕,,0,0,0,,即便苏提斯是当时世界上最快车手\N{\fs90}even though Surtees was clearly the fastest man available.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.01,0:57:09.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,我一气之下就开车走了\N{\fs90}And I just stormed away, drove back
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.89,0:57:12.55,字幕,,0,0,0,, 直接跟老头掰了\N{\fs90} and had it out with the old man.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.62,0:57:14.85,字幕,,0,0,0,,意大利的报纸是这么写的\N{\fs90}As the Italian papers put it,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.89,0:57:18.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,他们放了一张我走出大门的照片并写到\N{\fs90}they showed a picture of me walking out the gates and saying,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.02,0:57:23.86,字幕,,0,0,0,,约翰苏提斯和恩佐分道扬镳\N{\fs90}"The divorce of John Surtees and Enzo."
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.03,0:57:28.13,字幕,,0,0,0,,没有了苏提斯\N{\fs90}With Surtees out of the way,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.20,0:57:31.37,字幕,,0,0,0,,福特在排位赛中占据了前四\N{\fs90}the Fords took the top four slots in qualifying.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.44,0:57:33.16,字幕,,0,0,0,,随着时间的临近 \N{\fs90}And as the clock ticked down
Dialogue: 0,0:57:33.19,0:57:36.11,字幕,,0,0,0,,亨利福特二世准备为比赛挥旗开赛\N{\fs90}Henry Ford II prepared to drop the flag,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.15,0:57:37.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,同时祈祷着 这一次 \N{\fs90}praying that, this time
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.83,0:57:41.78,字幕,,0,0,0,,他能够如愿复仇\N{\fs90}he would get his revenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.88,0:57:45.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,从法国勒芒为您带来的 勒芒24小时耐力赛直播\N{\fs90}Live from Le Mans, France, it's the 24 Hours of Le Mans.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.36,0:58:00.90,字幕,,0,0,0,,一开始 福特迅速取得了领先\N{\fs90}At first, the Fords stormed into the lead.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.93,0:58:02.77,字幕,,0,0,0,,但没过几个小时\N{\fs90}But a few hours in,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.90,0:58:08.91,字幕,,0,0,0,,形势就仿佛要重演64年和65年的悲剧\N{\fs90}it was beginning to look like a depressing repeat of '64 and '65.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.91,0:58:11.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,随着夜幕降临 法拉利的赛车 凭借着更好的灵活性\N{\fs90}As night fell, the Ferraris, using their greater agility
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.81,0:58:13.71,字幕,,0,0,0,,和更高效的油耗\N{\fs90}and their greater fuel efficiency,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.78,0:58:15.81,字幕,,0,0,0,,排名上升到了第一第二位\N{\fs90}were leading the race one-two.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.91,0:58:20.99,字幕,,0,0,0,,8辆GT40中有4辆则无奈退赛\N{\fs90}Four of the eight GT40s were out of the race altogether.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.95,0:58:22.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,更糟糕的是 \N{\fs90}Worse still
Dialogue: 0,0:58:23.00,0:58:26.96,字幕,,0,0,0,,福特的车手们被明令禁止冒险驾驶\N{\fs90} the Ford drivers had strict orders not to go balls-out
Dialogue: 0,0:58:27.03,0:58:30.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,以保护赛车\N{\fs90}for fear of breaking the cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.49,0:58:33.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是有一个人无视了禁令\N{\fs90}But one man wasn't listening to those orders.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.63,0:58:35.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,肯迈尔斯没有保留\N{\fs90}Ken Miles put the hammer down,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.57,0:58:36.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,他的圈速一圈比一圈快 \N{\fs90}set blistering lap times
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.02,0:58:39.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,帮助福特重夺领先优势\N{\fs90}and retook the lead for Ford.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.70,0:58:43.94,字幕,,0,0,0,,法拉利的车手们根本跟不上这种节奏\N{\fs90}The Ferraris had no response to this crushing pace,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.94,0:58:48.15,字幕,,0,0,0,,到了早上 他们抛锚的抛锚 撞车的撞车\N{\fs90}and by morning, they had either broken down or crashed.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.98,0:58:50.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,那个下午 \N{\fs90}That afternoon
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.99,0:58:53.05,字幕,,0,0,0,,亨利福特亲眼目睹了\N{\fs90} Henry Ford watched his cars cruise home
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.12,0:58:56.45,字幕,,0,0,0,,他的车惊人的以包揽前三的排名从容地驶过终点\N{\fs90}to a spectacular one-two-three finish.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.56,0:59:03.63,字幕,,0,0,0,,第一名是二代福特GT\N{\fs90}First place for the Ford GT Mk II,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.69,0:59:07.80,字幕,,0,0,0,,这也是美国人第一次在勒芒取胜\N{\fs90}and a first-time win for America at Le Mans.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:07.87,0:59:11.97,字幕,,0,0,0,,福特在接下来的四届勒芒赛事中都取得了胜利\N{\fs90}Ford would go on to win their next four Le Mans races.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.97,0:59:15.14,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是那个为这支队伍付出的最多的人\N{\fs90}But the man who had contributed so much to the team
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.21,0:59:17.28,字幕,,0,0,0,,却没能看到这些胜利\N{\fs90}didn't get to see these triumphs.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:17.34,0:59:20.98,字幕,,0,0,0,,肯迈尔斯在第一年胜利后仅两个月\N{\fs90}Ken Miles was killed two months after their first win,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:21.01,0:59:24.43,字幕,,0,0,0,,便在测试新GT40时不幸身亡\N{\fs90}testing the latest GT40.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.98,0:59:29.59,字幕,,0,0,0,,我们无法得知亨利福特在对飙法拉利的三年中\N{\fs90}It's impossible to calculate how much Henry Ford spent
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.65,0:59:32.26,字幕,,0,0,0,,究竟花了多少钱\N{\fs90}on his three-year campaign to break Ferrari,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:32.32,0:59:34.56,字幕,,0,0,0,,有专家估计 最少的情况下\N{\fs90}but experts reckon that, at the very least,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.63,0:59:40.06,字幕,,0,0,0,,换算成今天的价格 也要3亿6千万英镑\N{\fs90}in today's money, it was £360 million.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.13,0:59:44.00,字幕,,0,0,0,,只因为跟暴脾气的意大利人发生了口角 就花这么多钱\N{\fs90}Now, that's a big bill for settling a spat with an angry Italian.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:46.00,0:59:48.54,字幕,,0,0,0,,但是想想我们从中的收获\N{\fs90}But look what we got out of it -
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.61,0:59:51.24,字幕,,0,0,0,,史上最佳车型之一\N{\fs90}one of the world's greatest cars.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.28,0:59:59.75,字幕,,0,0,0,,精彩\N{\fs90}Very good.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:59.82,1:00:01.72,字幕,,0,0,0,,真精彩 非常棒\N{\fs90}That was good. Very good.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:08.39,1:00:10.49,字幕,,0,0,0,,-我恨你 -我知道\N{\fs90}-I hate you. -I know.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.56,1:00:12.55,字幕,,0,0,0,,不 我现在真心恨你 \N{\fs90}No, but I really hate you now
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.58,1:00:15.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,因为你去开了福特GT40 而我没有\N{\fs90} cos you've driven a Ford GT40, and I never have.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.57,1:00:16.93,字幕,,0,0,0,,下周你打算怎样 \N{\fs90}I mean what is it next week
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.96,1:00:18.20,字幕,,0,0,0,,去舔海莲娜 克莉丝汀森马\N{\fs90} are you gonna lick helena christensen
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.27,1:00:19.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,听着\N{\fs90}Look...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.80,1:00:23.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,我确信GT40那车 如果你真想开也能开\N{\fs90}I'm sure you could drive a GT40 if you really wanted to.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.24,1:00:24.74,字幕,,0,0,0,,不行 我太高了\N{\fs90}I can't, I'm too tall.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:24.81,1:00:26.64,字幕,,0,0,0,,你的意思是太胖了吧\N{\fs90}Yeah, you mean fat.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.15,1:00:38.17,字幕,,0,0,0,,高\N{\fs90}Tall.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.23,1:00:40.39,字幕,,0,0,0,,横向的高吧\N{\fs90}Horizontally tall.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.59,1:00:43.79,字幕,,0,0,0,,听我说 别管是哪个维度\N{\fs90}Well, listen, whatever dimension is the problem,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.86,1:00:45.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,反正我就是开不了\N{\fs90}I can't drive one.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.46,1:00:47.40,字幕,,0,0,0,,随着这浓浓的失望 \N{\fs90}And on that terrible disappointment
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.44,1:00:48.50,字幕,,0,0,0,,今天的节目到此结束\N{\fs90} it is time to end.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:48.51,1:00:51.46,字幕,,0,0,0,,感谢各位的收看 晚安\N{\fs90}Thank you so much for watching. Good night.
